## Implementation notes for the new `install-linux.sh`

Keep the shape of the old script (set -euo pipefail, color logger,
`--help`/`--version`, log file). Differences from the v1.1.0 file that
matter:

- `INSTALL_PREFIX` default → `${AG_HOME:-$HOME/.local/share/ag}`. Match
  `PathManager::get_base_dir` exactly so the installer's directories are
  the ones the running binary actually uses. Drop the
  `documents.db`/`memory.db` touch — those aren't real schemas; let the
  app create what it needs on first boot.
- Subdirs: `data index db logs cache locks config` (mirror PathManager,
  plus a `config/` slot for `.env`).
- Don't touch `~/.bashrc`/`.zshrc`. Instead write `${AG_HOME}/config/.env`
  by copying `.env.example` and overwriting `BACKEND_HOST`/`BACKEND_PORT`
  and `AG_HOME` if `--backend-port`/`--prefix` are passed. Print a one-
  liner telling the user how to `export AG_HOME=...` for their shell.
- Backend build: `cargo build --release` from the repo root (workspace
  default-member is `backend`, so this builds `ag`). Verify
  `target/release/ag` exists; print its size.
- Frontend build (default; skip with `--no-frontend`): `cd frontend/fro &&
  npm ci && npm run css:build && trunk build --release`. Refuse with a
  clear error if `trunk` or `npm` is missing — don't try to install them.
- Docker stack (default; skip with `--no-stack`, select with
  `--with-stack=PROFILE`): require `docker` on PATH. Run
  `docker compose -f docker-compose.yml --profile "$PROFILE" up -d`. Empty
  profile (the default) = all services (matches the compose file's
  `profiles: ["", ...]` convention).
- Systemd (default; skip with `--no-systemd`): use `sed` to template
  `systemd/ag-full-stack.service`:
  - `WorkingDirectory=/home/pde/ag` → `WorkingDirectory=$PROJECT_PATH`
  - `ExecStart=/home/pde/ag/start-ag.sh` → `ExecStart=$PROJECT_PATH/start-ag.sh`
  Add `Environment=AG_HOME=$INSTALL_PREFIX` and
  `Environment=BACKEND_PORT=$BACKEND_PORT` so the unit picks up the
  installer's choices. Install as `~/.config/systemd/user/ag.service`,
  then `daemon-reload`, `enable --now`. Don't enable lingering — that's a
  separate user decision.
- Health check: poll `http://127.0.0.1:${BACKEND_PORT}/health` up to 10x
  at 2s intervals. Treat "no response" as a warning, not a hard failure,
  because the user might have passed `--no-systemd` and not started the
  service themselves yet.
- Don't run `cargo test` as part of install. That's what the
  user's quality-gate (`cargo fmt && cargo clippy`) is for and it doubles
  install time. The old script did this; we drop it.
- Don't try to start a verification `cargo run` and then `kill` it (the
  old script's "post-build verification"). It's fragile, it racially
  fights with systemd if `--with-systemd` is in play, and the health
  check covers the same need.

## Flags

```
./installers/install-linux.sh [OPTIONS]

  --project-path PATH    Repo path (default: $PWD)
  --prefix PATH          AG_HOME (default: $AG_HOME or ~/.local/share/ag)
  --backend-port PORT    BACKEND_PORT (default: 3010)
  --mode release|debug   cargo build profile (default: release)
  --no-systemd           Skip installing ~/.config/systemd/user/ag.service
  --no-stack             Skip docker compose up
  --with-stack=PROFILE   Compose profile (core | observability | "" = all,
                         default "")
  --no-frontend          Skip npm ci + css:build + trunk build in frontend/fro
  --skip-checks          Skip preflight tool checks
  --verbose              set -x
  --version, --help

By default (no flags): does all four — backend build, frontend build,
docker compose up -d (all profiles), and systemd --user enable --now.
```

## Verification

After implementation, sanity-check on this machine:

1. `bash installers/install-linux.sh --help` prints the new help.
2. `bash installers/install-linux.sh` (no flags) from the repo root —
   the full path:
   - creates `~/.local/share/ag/{data,index,db,logs,cache,locks,config}`
   - writes `~/.local/share/ag/config/.env` if absent
   - builds `target/release/ag`
   - builds frontend at `frontend/fro/dist/`
   - `docker ps` shows ag-redis (and the observability containers) up
   - installs `~/.config/systemd/user/ag.service` with the templated
     `WorkingDirectory` matching `$PWD`
   - `systemctl --user status ag.service` reports active
   - health probe to `http://127.0.0.1:3010/health` returns 200 within
     ~20s
3. `bash installers/install-linux.sh --no-stack --no-systemd --no-frontend`
   reduces to "build only": creates dirs + .env, builds the backend, does
   NOT touch docker or systemd or `frontend/fro/dist/`.
4. `bash installers/install-linux.sh --with-stack=core --no-systemd
   --no-frontend` brings only Redis + Ollama up.
5. `bash installers/uninstall-linux.sh` reverses (2): stops + disables
   `ag.service`, removes the unit file, optionally `docker compose down`.
   `--purge` also deletes `~/.local/share/ag`.
6. `cargo fmt && cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings` still pass
   (no Rust code touched, but run it as the project's quality gate
   demands).
